Q1 : What is JDK vs JRE vs JVM vs JIT? 
Ans : JDK - Jdk stands for java development kit it is responsible for developing java application. 
jdk contains several other tools like jre,  jvm and and other libraries. 

JRE - JRE stands for java runtime environment. Jre provides runtime environment to run our 
byte code (.class file)

JVM - JVM stands for java virtual machine it is part of jre software it is responsible for 
executing java program. jvm will allocate memory required for program execution and jvm will 
also deallocate the object when it(object) is not in use. jvm will convert byte code into machine 
code.

JIT stands for just in time, it is a compiler. Jit runs along with the interpretor.JIT is a part of 
execution engine in jvm architecture, jit runs the repeated code and interpreter runs the code line by 
line. it is also responsible to convert .class file into machine code, so the performance(of execution 
engine) become faster. 

for example : if a method is to be called more than once so first time interpreter will 
interprete this code line by line and from 2nd time when we call the method again 
jit will compile this whole method no need of interpretor. All it internally takes care.      

      

