Why we use deep copy ? 
To duplicate the data because when u are unsure about the source/address because it can be removed address can be removed 
Uncertainty in memory location thats why we use deep copy 


Shallow copy is a technique to refer to the data at readily available memory location 
A shallow copy means: it copies the object, but not deeply.
But if the object has references to other objects, then only the reference is copied, not the actual object.
So → both original and copy will point to the same inner object.

Why do we use shallow copy? 
No need to duplicate the data


